solutions.content:
It is a simple conversion question.
The angle between hour and minute hand = angle from 12 o'clock to hour hand - angle from 12 o'clock to minutes hand

angle from 12 o'clock to hour hand = ((5*hour + (minutes/60)*5))/60)*360 [because hour hand will be slightly moved in clockwise direction because of minutes passed and also converting to degrees]

angle from 12 o'clock to minutes hand = (minutes/60)*360

On simplification we get,
angle between hour hand and minutes hand = 30*hour - 5.5*minutes

Because we should take the smaller angle, we use the min function to find the minimum of (angle, 360 - angle)

NOTE: The result angle could be negative so we take the absolute value

 ```
class Solution {
public:
    double angleClock(int hour, int minutes) {
        double ans = abs(30*hour - (5.5*minutes));
        return min(ans, 360-ans);
    }
};
```

