# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
    Problem can be solved using simple bfs.
    Adjacent vertices of node i = [i+1, i-1, k] where arr[i] = arr[k];
    time[j] = Needs minimum time to reach possition j.
    We need to jump only if(time[i]+1 < time[j]) means the node j not explored yet.



# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minJumps(vector<int>& arr) {
        int n = size(arr);
        map<int,vector<int>> graph;
        vector<int> time(n,1e9);
        queue<int> q;
        q.push(0); time[0] = 0;
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++) graph[arr[i]].push_back(i);
        while(!q.empty()){
            int i = q.front(); q.pop();
            auto & v = graph[arr[i]];
            v.push_back(i-1), v.push_back(i+1);
            for(auto & j : v){
                if(j>=0 && j<n && time[j] > time[i]+1) time[j] = time[i]+1, q.push(j);
            }
            v.clear();
        }
        return time[n-1];
    }
};
```

